    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-google-discovers-images"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google finds images through 3 primary paths. The Googlebot crawler follows links on your pages and discovers <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> elements in your HTML. Image sitemaps provide a direct list of image URLs for the crawler to process. And the Google Images bot specifically <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/google-images">crawls pages</a> looking for visual content.</p></div></div>
  </div>
