      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-google-understands-image-content"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google uses multiple signals to understand what an image shows. The file name provides initial context. <a href="/glossary/alt-text/">Alt text</a> acts as the primary description signal. Surrounding page content, captions, and headings add topical relevance.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
